<h2 id="weather-nature">Weather and Nature Sounds</h2>

<p>Japanese has specific onomatopoeia for different types of rain, wind, and natural phenomena:</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>ザーザー</strong> (zaa zaa) — Heavy, pouring rain</li>
  <li><strong>しとしと</strong> (shito shito) — Gentle, quiet rain</li>
  <li><strong>パラパラ</strong> (para para) — Light scattered rain</li>
  <li><strong>ビュービュー</strong> (byuu byuu) — Strong howling wind</li>
  <li><strong>そよそよ</strong> (soyo soyo) — Gentle breeze</li>
  <li><strong>ゴロゴロ</strong> (goro goro) — Rolling thunder</li>
  <li><strong>チラチラ</strong> (chira chira) — Snow fluttering down</li>
</ul>

